      Which is nut and which is Bolt?
      Bolts and nuts are nearly always used together to fasten a stack of parts together. 3. A nut is a small metallic object, whereas a bolt is basically a screw. 4. A nut is a small hexagonal object made out of metal.

      What is the difference between nuts and bolts? - Quora

      www.quora.com › What-is-the-difference-between-nuts-a...
      www.quora.com › What-is-the-difference-between-nuts-a...
      Search for: Which is nut and which is Bolt?
      What is a bolt used for?
      A bolt is a type of fastener, usually made from metal, that commonly comprises a head at one end, a chamfer at the other, and a shaft characterised by an external helical ridge known as a 'thread'. Bolts are typically used to hold materials or objects together, or to position objects.Mar 20, 2020
